trespass.annotation

Annotation Type ProxyClass


  • @Target(value=TYPE)
@Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface ProxyClass

    This annotation is mandatory for proxy interfaces extending Trespasser and defines the target class for the proxy interface.

    Version:
    $Revision$
    Author:
    Eduardo Rodrigues

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      java.lang.String targetClassName
      Fully qualified name of the target class for the annotated interface
      java.lang.Class<?> value
      The annotated interface's target Class definition.

        public abstract java.lang.Class<?> value
        The annotated interface's target Class definition. When not available or accessible at compile time, then the class' fully qualified name can be specified via targetClassName()
        Default:
        trespass.annotation.ProxyClass.class
